node.text:
@EssiNutrition 

LAUNCHING• 10•1•21 @12PM PST

The day has finally come to announce something I’ve been working on for so long!😭 Through all the trial and error, sourcing a GMP manufacturer, brand development, creating the formulas, owning and financially backing this new company was my goal! 

There are 3 products launching that I’ll be talking about more in depth PUMP, POWER-PUMP & SERENITY! PUMP & POWER PUMP will release with 2 amazing and unique flavors- Watermelon Paradise & Coconut Berry!🍉🥥

I have so many big plans for this company & supplements lined up to launch throughout the year! This supplement line will be a full range as soon as we can put products out!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jessica Arevalo on September 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, biceps and standing.

node.text:
SAVE THIS FULL UPPER BODY WORKOUT!😤
-
1. Incline dumbbell chest press 3 sets 12 reps.
-
2. Front dumbbell raise superset side lateral raise 3 sets 15 reps.
-
3. Neutral grip pull down 3 sets 15 reps slow and controller with 1 second pause.
-
4. Straight arm rear delt fly 15 reps superset bent arm 10 reps 3 sets.
-
5. Smith machine military press behind the head superset seated dumb bell curls 3 sets 12-15 reps.
-
6. Cable lat pull downs superset tricep extensions 3 sets 15 reps 
-
Note: I always warm up with 1 set and then move on to my working sets.
-
Outfit details: @jessicaarevalocollection

node.text:
I want to ask y’all what you see when you see this picture? A pretty girl that looks happy, healthy and fit, right? I always get so many messages from all of you saying how perfect and beautiful I am. I am always so humbled and grateful for your messages. But sometimes I feel sad because I know it’s rarely how I feel on the inside. Most people judge you by the way you appear on the outside before ever really thinking of what that person feels like on the inside. 

Social media has created this perfect image of people because most people will only show the good that is going on in their world. Which is far from real life and the truth. I have always done my best to share my life and be very open and vulnerable to you all because I know I can’t be the only one going through anxiety and depression. I come from a broken home, abusive relationships verbally, physically and emotionally and sexually as a kid and as an adult. I was clinically diagnosed with severe depression and have often thought about ending it all because sometimes the pain inside feels unbearable. Everyday I wake up and sometimes I have the strength to tackle my day head on and sometimes I don’t. I try to remind myself that it’s ok… I am human and not a robot. 

I want you all to know that no matter how down you are feeling, just know that there are many others in the same boat as you, including myself. The most important thing is TO NEVER GIVE UP! No matter how hard it may seem, you have to keep going because there is strength inside of you that you don’t know you have yet! I am living proof that no matter what background you come from you can still come out on top and surpass all of your dreams through courage and a relentless heart! I love you all and I just had it on my heart to share this with you! 

TAG SOMEONE THAT NEEDS TO HEAR THIS MESSAGE💕

node.text:
SAVE THIS HAMSTRING FOCUSED WORKOUT!🍑
-
I always stretch and foam roll before any exercise and do at least 1 warm up set before actual working sets.
-
1. RDL - 3 sets 12-15 reps - 35-50lbs.
-
2. Lying leg curls - 3 sets - 15 reps - 50-70lbs - Pause at the top for 1 second and slowly lower down. 
-
3. Leg press with foot placement high and shoulder width apart. 3 sets 15-20 reps.
-
4. Glute machine kickback - 3 sets 15-20 reps 50-75lbs.
-
5. Abductors with butt off the seat - 3 sets 15-20 reps 50-60lbs.
-
Shorts| @jessicaarevalocollection

node.text:
1,2 OR 3?📸
-
Is Throwback Thursday still a thing?🤷🏻‍♀️
-
I’ve been on Instagram over a decade now!😱🤣 I know I know I’m old! These pictures I took from Greece a few weeks back! 
-
Physique update photos coming soon! I weighed about 116lbs here but have since lost even more weight. The goal is to get around 110-112lbs and see how I look/feel and adjust from there! 
-
This journey hasn’t been easy but the results have def been worth it! Not just physically but mentally as well!💪🏼

node.text:
SAVE THIS FULL UPPER BODY WORKOUT!💪🏼
-

1. Single arm lat pull down - 3 sets 12-15 reps 

2. Incline dumbbell press - 3 sets 15 reps 

3. Single arm rear delt cable fly drop set to bent elbow - 3 sets 10/10 reps 

4. Chest supported front raise SS lateral raises - 3 sets 15 reps 

5. Seated shoulder press SS front seated shoulder press 3 sets 12-15 reps

6. Overhead tricep extensions 3 sets 12-15 reps 
-
Outfit details @jessicaarevalocollection

node.text:
This is 36! 🤍 🥳

My birthday was 8.27.85. Feeling so incredibly blessed with another year to learn and grow as a woman. I was surrounded by my favorite people in my life MY FAMILY & FRIENDS! (Stay tuned for bday spam).

Thank you to everyone that spent this special day with me it truly,truly meant the world that y’all made it! Cheers to another year of HEALTH & HAPPINESS!

Also thank YOU for all the birthday messages, texts, DMS, etc. I truly felt special this year!❤️
